 draw a figure or any other object to look 24 bracciahigh you must do it in this way. First, on the surface _m r_ drawha
lf the man you wish to represent; then the other half; then put onthe vault _m n_ [the rest of] the figure spoken of abo
ve; first setout the vertical plane on the floor of a room of the same shape asthe wall with the coved part on which you
 are to paint your figure.Then, behind it, draw a figure set out in profile of whatever sizeyou please, and draw lines f
rom it to the point _f_ and, as theselines cut _m n_ on the vertical plane, so will the figure come onthe wall, of which
 the vertical plane gives a likeness, and you willhave all the [relative] heights and prominences of the figure. Andthe
breadth or thickness which are on the upright wall _m n_ are tobe drawn in their proper form, since, as the wall recedes
 the figurewill be foreshortened by itself; but [that part of] the figure whichgoes into the cove you must foreshorten,
