Studies for a form of a Church most proper for preaching.The problem as to what form of church might answer the requirem
entsof acoustics seems to have engaged Leonardo's very particularattention. The designation of_ "teatro" _given to some
of thesesketches, clearly shows which plan seemed to him most favourable forhearing the preacher's voice.Pl. XCVII, No.
1 (MS. B, 52). Rectangular edifice divided into threenaves with an apse on either side, terminated by a semicircularthea
tre with rising seats, as in antique buildings. The pulpit is inthe centre. Leonardo has written on the left side of the
 sketch_:"teatro da predicare" _(Theatre for preaching).MS. B, 55a (see page 56, Fig. 1). A domed church after the type
ofPl. XCV, No. 1, shows four theatres occupying the apses and facingthe square_ "coro" _(choir), which is in the centre
