y of extreme leanness and extreme fatness.The divisions of the head (812. 813).812.ANATOMY.There are eleven elementary t
issues:-- Cartilage, bones, nerves,veins, arteries, fascia, ligament and sinews, skin, muscle and fat.OF THE HEAD.The di
visions of the head are 10, viz. 5 external and 5 internal,the external are the hair, skin, muscle, fascia and the skull
; theinternal are the dura mater, the pia mater, [which enclose] thebrain. The pia mater and the dura mater come again u
nderneath andenclose the brain; then the rete mirabile, and the occipital bone,which supports the brain from which the n
erves spring.813._a_. hair_n_. skin_c_. muscle_m_. fascia_o_. skull _i.e._ bone_b_. dura mater_d_. pia mater_f_. brain_r
