qual distance, that undergoesleast diminution which at first was most remote.When various objects are removed at equal d
istances farther fromtheir original position, that which was at first the farthest fromthe eye will diminish least. And
the proportion of the diminutionwill be in proportion to the relative distance of the objects fromthe eye before they we
re removed.That is to say in the object _t_ and the object _e_ the proportionof their distances from the eye _a_ is quin
tuple. I remove each fromits place and set it farther from the eye by one of the 5 parts intowhich the proposition is di
vided. Hence it happens that the nearestto the eye has doubled the distance and according to the lastproposition but one
 of this, is diminished by the half of its wholesize; and the body _e_, by the same motion, is diminished 1/5 of itswhol
