The ebb and flow of the tide (955-960).955.Where there is a larger quantity of water, there is a greater flowand ebb, bu
t the contrary in narrow waters.Look whether the sea is at its greatest flow when the moon is halfway over our hemispher
e [on the meridian].956.Whether the flow and ebb are caused by the moon or the sun, or arethe breathing of this terrestr
ial machine. That the flow and ebb aredifferent in different countries and seas.[Footnote: 1. Allusion may here be made
to the mythologicalexplanation of the ebb and flow given in the Edda. Utgardloki saysto Thor (Gylfaginning 48): "When th
ou wert drinking out of the horn,and it seemed to thee that it was slow in emptying a wonder befell,which I should not h
ave believed possible: the other end of the hornlay in the sea, which thou sawest not; but when thou shalt go to thesea,
