e Dardanelles.1108.In the Bosphorus the Black Sea flows always into the Egean sea, andthe Egean sea never flows into it.
 And this is because the Caspian,which is 400 miles to the East, with the rivers which pour into it,always flows through
 subterranean caves into this sea of Pontus; andthe Don does the same as well as the Danube, so that the waters ofPontus
 are always higher than those of the Egean; for the higheralways fall towards the lower, and never the lower towards the
