only that he had given him two gunsto clean. Afterwards, when I had urged him farther, be left theworkshop and began to
work in his room, and lost much time in makinganother pair of pincers and files and other tools with screws; andthere he
 worked at mills for twisting silk which he hid when any oneof my people went in, and with a thousand oaths and mutterin
