ength,height and form of what he had to do; and so we remained inill-will.The next thing was that he made himself anothe
r workshop and pincersand tools in his room where he slept, and there he worked forothers; afterwards he went to dine wi
th the Swiss of the guard,where there are idle fellows, in which he beat them all; and mosttimes they went two or three
