e country, not without payment; and each one grates his portionvery fine, and puts it upon the first food he eats; and t
husbelieves that by faith he has eaten his saint who then preserves himfrom all perils. What do you think here, Man, of
your own species?Are you so wise as you believe yourselves to be? Are these things tobe done by men?1359.As I told you i
